# Brokered-tool fail-fast on isError (Tier 2 / REQ-107).
#
# When a brokered tool returns `CallToolResult { isError: true, ... }`, the
# macro frame raises `fail` immediately via `formatToolError` — it does
# NOT bind the error message as a value (POC Probe 10). This is the
# default semantics for v1; a future `try`-form may opt into recoverable
# behavior, but the vast majority of macros benefit from fail-fast.
#
# Run this example expecting exit code 1 with the canonical
# `tool_call_failed` envelope from the runner (REQ-054 / REQ-024 ac5).
#
# Run:
#   npx tsx src/run.ts examples/24-brokered-fail-fast.fqm
#
# Expected output:
#   TOOL CALL FAILED:
#   { "error": "tool_call_failed", "message": "brokered tool coerce_demo.is_error failed (is_error_result): synthetic upstream failure: demo isError path", ... }

echo "Calling a brokered tool that returns isError:true …"
echo "The macro frame should fail-fast — anything after this never runs."

result = coerce_demo.is_error()

# UNREACHABLE — REQ-107 raises MacroFailError on the isError path BEFORE
# any value is bound.
echo "ERROR: this line should never execute (isError didn't fail-fast)"
echo "got: $result"
exit { unreachable: true }
